OL,3,CD-Day veterans honour those lost with
OL,4,C'emotional' ferry crossing to Normandy
OL,6,FSitting on deck, 98-year-old Henry
OL,7,FRice told me what he remembered of his
OL,8,Fjourney to Normandy at the age of 18:
OL,9,F"I was 50% excited, 50% apprehensive."
OL,11,FHis job was to take out supplies and
OL,12,Fbring back the wounded.
OL,14,F"I was half expecting shells and
OL,15,Fbullets and U-boats ... but I got away
OL,16,Fwith it," Mr Rice said.
OL,18,F"It's the thought of those lads that
OL,19,Fare still lying over there, those that
OL,20,Fgave their lives. I survived and they
OL,21,Fdidn't. That's what I'm doing this for.
