OL,3,CD-Day veterans honour those lost with
OL,4,C'emotional' ferry crossing to Normandy
OL,6,F"It's a journey that I will make until
OL,7,FI can't make it."
OL,9,FThousands of allied troops were killed
OL,10,Fon D Day alone, as they fought their
OL,11,Fway onto Normandy's beaches.
OL,13,FIt was the biggest seaborne invasion
OL,14,Fin history and, ultimately, a moment
OL,15,Fthat helped to turn the tide against
OL,16,Ftheir enemy.
OL,18,FAlec Penstone, 99, remembers it like
OL,19,Fit was yesterday.
