OL,3,CD-Day veterans honour those lost with
OL,4,C'emotional' ferry crossing to Normandy
OL,6,FHe told me that his job, as a
OL,7,Fsubmarine detector, was to stop German
OL,8,FU-boats from attacking Allied boats as
OL,9,Fthey made their way towards Normandy.
OL,11,F"And we managed it!" he exclaimed.
OL,13,FI asked him if he was proud of what he
OL,14,Fachieved that day, to which he
OL,15,Fresponded: "Yes, definitely. Without a
OL,16,Fdoubt. Until I saw the rows of graves
OL,17,Fof the ones that didn't make it.
OL,18,FThey're the real heroes.
